plot: A jet-propelled white rabbit flies through the vulva of a supine woman into a wonderland where people and objects turn inside out, changing shapes and identities at warp speed. Events roughly follow Lewis Carroll's &"Alice in Wonderland.&" The caterpillar and the queen make appearances, as does Alice. Images and symbols are often sexual. At the end, Alice asks, &"Who has had such a curious dream?&"   Written by
title: Malice in Wonderland
